{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A man who isolates himself seeks his own desire;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He rages against all wise judgment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A fool has no delight in understanding,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But in expressing his own heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When the wicked comes, contempt comes also;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And with dishonor comes reproach."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The words of a man's mouth are deep waters;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The wellspring of wisdom is a flowing brook."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is not good to show partiality to the wicked,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Or to overthrow the righteous in judgment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A fool's lips enter into contention,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And his mouth calls for blows."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A fool's mouth is his destruction,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And his lips are the snare of his soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The words of a talebearer are like tasty trifles,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they go down into the inmost body."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who is slothful in his work Is a brother to him who is a great destroyer."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The name of the Lord is a strong tower;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The righteous run to it and are safe."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The rich man's wealth is his strong city,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And like a high wall in his own esteem."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Before destruction the heart of a man is haughty,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And before honor is humility."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who answers a matter before he hears it, It is folly and shame to him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The spirit of a man will sustain him in sickness,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But who can bear a broken spirit?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The heart of the prudent acquires knowledge,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the ear of the wise seeks knowledge."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A man's gift makes room for him,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And brings him before great men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The first one to plead his cause seems right,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Until his neighbor comes and examines him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Casting lots causes contentions to cease,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And keeps the mighty apart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A brother offended is harder to win than a strong city,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And contentions are like the bars of a castle."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A man's stomach shall be satisfied from the fruit of his mouth;"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "From the produce of his lips he shall be filled."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Death and life are in the power of the tongue,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And those who love it will eat its fruit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He who finds a wife finds a good thing,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And obtains favor from the Lord."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The poor man uses entreaties,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But the rich answers roughly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A man who has friends must himself be friendly,"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}